author: andreasmyth
msg: System handlers can be bracketed around logical and protocol JAX-WS handlers. They are created along with the client/server binding and are not affected by calls to Binding.setHandlerChain in application code. Can be configured via Celtix configuration only (on port and endpoint resp.).
Refactored handler chain configuration from annotations to use the same mechanisms as for Celtix cfg files.
Allowed execution of tests named Abstract...Test(Case).java (surefire excludes them by default).
